Some aircraft systems still use electron tubes in their equipment.  And a large of old model aircrafts that are still in service use vacuum electron tubes in their application.  
   Originally electron tubes were developped to be used for radio application. \xa0  
  They were used in radio transmitters as oscillators for generating audio as amplifiers for controlling voltage and current, also as radio frequency signals, \xa0and as rectifiers for converting alternating current into direct current. \xa0  
  For avionics application \xa0mainly 4 kind of electron were used: Triodes – diodes – Tetrodes and Pentodes.
